Step 1:

First finding the unique API_UUID and Revisions_created from below table

SELECT * FROM COCT42_AM.AM_API

Step 2:

Any how we have unique API_UUID in table COCT42_AM.AM_API

SELECT distinct(API_UUID) FROM COCT42_AM.AM_API ; -- 2249
SELECT count(*) FROM COCT42_AM.AM_API ; -- 2249

So do not need to filter anything here

Step 3:

Now you have unique API_UUID and its Revisions_created (always need to refer this in the flow)

3.1 Now I need to look for each unique API_UUID and Revisions_created

    /_system/governance/apimgt/applicationdata/apis/{API_UUID}/{Revisions_created}

    SELECT   r.reg_content_id,  r.reg_uuid,  r.reg_name,  r.reg_media_type,  p.reg_path_value,  r.reg_last_updated_time
    FROM coct42_reg.reg_resource r
    JOIN coct42_reg.reg_path p
      ON r.reg_path_id = p.reg_path_id
    WHERE    p.reg_path_value LIKE '%/_system/governance/apimgt/applicationdata/apis/{API_UUID}/{Revisions_created}%'
     and r.reg_name = 'api'
    ORDER BY r.reg_last_updated_time DESC;

